ate,I took by th'' throat the circumcised dogAnd smote him thus.', 13, 0), (337322, 'Love the people who love you back.', 13110, 0), (337323, 'So may the New Year be a happy one to you, happy to many more whose happiness depends on you!', 96, 0), (337324, 'Nothing gives a sadder sense of decay than this loss or suspension of the power to deal with unaccustomed things, and to keep up with the swiftness of the passing moment. [Speaking of self-posed isolation in old age.]', 650, 0), (337325, 'The fools among us are presented to be wise and the wise among us are presented to be fools.', 88, 0), (337326, 'Smartass Disciple: My master, please show me how to be a wise man!Master of Stupidity: I can''t. But I can show you how to do something wisely.', 1296, 0), (337327, 'Beware the irrational, however seductive. Shun the ‘transcendent’ and all who invite you to subordinate or annihilate yourself. Don’t be afraid to be thought arrogant or selfish. Picture all experts as if they were mammals. Never be a spectator of unfairness or stupidity. Seek out argument and disputation for their own sake; the grave will provide plenty of time for silence.', 1188, 0), (337328, 'if a sheep eats bushes does it eat flowers too?a sheep eats whatever it findseven a flower with thorn?even a flower with thorns.then what''s the good of thorns?', 69, 0), (337329, 'What makes you wise is not what you learn, but what you practice. What makes you wealthy is not what you earn, but what you invest. So, invest in what to practice, and practice what to invest.', 55137, 0), (337330, 'The only way to see everything, my dear, is to see it absolutely.', 55138, 0), (337331, 'Lead looked to his hand and saw sparkling chunks of glass in the cracks of the road. He saw ants running around the cracks, infinitely small. His blood ran into the cracks, creating rivers for the industrious ants to perplex over. Lead smiled at the creatures, for he understood that there is no difference between them and us in their wanderings and labor.', 55139, 0), (337332, 'Least said,soonest mended," Toby quipped, quoting a saying Jess often used.', 9672, 0), (337333, 'A wise warrior learns from her mistakes.', 361, 0), (337334, 'This was a freedom essential to the health even of a character so little susceptible of morbid influences as that of Phoebe. The old house [with dry rot in its structure and perhaps also in its inhabitants]', 55140, 0), (337335, 'Happy are those who love for they are loved by God! Alleluia! Amen!', 6223, 0), (337336, 'Intelligence is loving what is good and Wisdom is worshiping the One True Living God (FGL)! Alleluia! Amen!', 6223, 0), (337337, 'Happy are you who love for you are loved by God! Alleluia! Amen!', 6223, 0), (337338, 'All things under heaven are now in God''s supervision for all eternity! Alleluia! Amen!', 6223, 0), (337339, 'All good things remain forever for it is God''s plan for all eternity! Alleluia! Amen! ', 6223, 0), (337340, 'Help means give me a hand.', 2878, 0), (337341, 'Hester glowered at her. “The biggest mistake a villain can make is to get caught up in revenge. Hansel and Gretel were two hungry kids trying to survive in the Woods. Mother thought she’d captured another pair of greedy, gluttonous brats, only to grossly underestimate them. Hansel and Gretel killed her because they had to. It wasn’t personal.” She glanced back at the old siblings. “Doesn’t mean I can stand the sight of ’em, of course. But it also doesn’t mean their story has anything to do with mine anymore.', 7787, 0), (337342, 'Perhaps we are not really sinners in the hands of an angry God, after all. Perhaps we are all more like seedlings in the hands of a wise gardener.', 7602, 0), (337343, 'A wise man lays up treasures in the Kingdom of our Father, so as to live a happy eternal life', 3800, 0), (337344, 'It''s a fine thing to be clever, but too much cleverness usually produces the same result as ignorance.-Lady Berwick', 31, 0), (337345, 'Oh, Gilbert, don''t let''s ever grow too old and wise... no, not too old and silly for fairyland.', 250, 0), (337346, 'Wise are those who keep asking questions when everyone around them think they know the answers.', 50864, 0), (337347, 'It is wise to consider a matter carefully before jumping in carelessly.', 10427, 0), (337348, 'Don''t be afraid to be weird for being wise.', 3962, 0), (337349, 'I have plenty of time... if I am not wise... I could lose it like the games in which you gamble.', 4605, 0), (337350, 'Jokes are another example of stupidity... we are so wise and so clever and we do stupid stuff, how wise is that?Jokes on stage of being serious... when you aren''t serious what you get is more likely somebody being in state of seriousness.', 4605, 0);
