w far did we reach, it''s incrediable view out here,... but one thing is missing isn''t out this have something near, overall after all?', 4605, 0), (337365, 'The wisdom to be on the throne of one’s life must surpass the wisdom of the one being ruled, otherwise I will squander the whole of my life in the most appalling ways. By virtue of that reality, I would be wise to get out of the chair and invite God to have a seat.', 4397, 0), (337366, 'I should avoid that emotion, when I laugh I always think that I''m somehow an a guy who lowers his IQ.', 4605, 0), (337367, 'Make this moment magnificent!', 2878, 0), (337368, 'How can she? She''s incapable of understanding anything. Besides, do any of us understand what we are doing? If we did, would we ever do it?', 266, 0), (337369, 'Looking for positives is always wise in any situation that you may encounter.', 11173, 0), (337370, 'The greatest realization is dawn of my sacred existence.', 2878, 0), (337371, 'Be wise and walk with the wise.', 2878, 0), (337372, 'Be wise enough, know when to move on.', 2878, 0), (337373, 'It seems to me that smart people seem to know things and wise people know how to use what they know. Smart is a big help to a man', 55144, 0), (337374, 'A wise man does not waste so good a commodity as lying for naught.', 286, 0), (337375, 'As my father used to say: “There are two sure ways to lose a friend, one is to borrow, the other to lend.” - Kvothe the Bloodless (The Name of The Wind)', 313, 0), (337376, 'we are all half fool, half wise , there is no wisdom without foolishness and no pride without shame .', 260, 0), (337377, 'It''s the deep breath before the plunge.', 65, 0), (337378, 'How can the nation be mightier, without unity of its citizens?', 2878, 0), (337379, 'The duel may go on for long, but the self-defense often wins over the self-reproach.', 11038, 0), (337380, 'We are living in a world where Ignorance is celebrated as wisdom and Wisdom sidelined as Ignorance.', 10680, 0), (337381, 'If you want to be educated and wise, you must open your heart, expand your mind, be accepting and ready to change.', 2586, 0), (337382, 'Portia followed after, a smirk on her face, and Syc hissed as he passed.Donegan waited till they were gone, then swung round to Gracious."He hissed at me.""He hissed at you.""Should I hiss back?""It''s a bit late.""He could still hear.""Not unless you run after him.""Do you think I should?""Probably not.""I think I should.""It''d be a bit weird.""You might be right." Donegan pursed his lips, then shook his fist at the doorway."That showed him," said Gracious.Donegan nodded. "He''ll think twice about hissing at me again.', 1555, 0), (337383, '...But I''ve felt your grief, your loss. And though your species is capable of horrors, it''s capable of beauty, too. To end it now would be no better than taking your dreams away; to bring death robs your species of the chance to heal.', 2643, 0), (337384, 'Library: The Temple of the Wise!', 3701, 0), (337385, 'Better to be able to love than to be loveable.', 6509, 0), (337386, 'Even the wisest and the best of us can be foolish occasionally.', 591, 0), (337387, 'It takes a year to be collectively known as "intelligent" but it takes a lifetime to be distinguished as "wise', 55145, 0), (337388, 'Let there be spaces in your togetherness.And let the wind of the heavens dance between you.', 81, 0), (337389, 'Vacation time is something we all accrue, but only the wisest of us recognize its importance.', 27097, 0), (337390, 'Time cannot be saved, it can only be spent, and if not spent wisely and well, it is wasted.', 25350, 0), (337391, 'Many people die long before their departure date, Through ignorance of living a life they never wanted to be apart of but are to scared to change.', 3305, 0), (337392, 'The most difficult thing in the world is to know how to do a thing and to watch someone else do it wrong without comment', 17594, 0), (337393, 'Advantages never comes free. You have to create it the way you want it!', 11203, 0), (337394, 'The knowledge we need, we are predisposed to seeking, intuitively.A fool does not know, what to do with importance, how to gauge importance, but they readily seek influence.The corrupt didn''t find the expanse of life giving thought, because their self is their center; the stagnant find it hard to revolve.The wise do not subscribe to the fodder that feeds the herd, because they are not predisposed to being swept along in banal minutiae.', 10831, 0), (337395, 'The boy gathers materials for a temple, and then when he is thirty, concludes to build a woodshed', 1049, 0), (337396, 'You never too old to Become wiser !T.B', 37879, 0), (337397, 'Wise words are like seeds. The more you scatter them, the more they will grow into infinite gardens of knowledge.', 2678, 0), (337398, 'Schooling gives you knowledge, but education makes you wise.', 2586, 0), (337399, 'To be knowledgeable, learn new things every day; to be wise, unlearn things that you learn with wit and love.', 2586, 0), (337400, 'In medical science, as in daily life, it was unwise to jump to conclusions', 532, 0);
