er them, looked grim on early falling nights, but Ingleside bloomed with firelight and laughter, though the winds come in from the Atlantic singing of mournful things. "Why isn''t the wind happy, Mummy?" asked Walter one night. "Because it is remembering all the sorrow of the world since it began," answered Anne.', 250, 0), (337435, 'When we learn how to become resilient, we learn how to embrace the beautifully broad spectrum of the human experience.', 721, 0), (337436, 'The problem is that we always look for the missing piece of the puzzle instead of finding a place for the one in our hand...', 30636, 0), (337437, 'The well bred contradict other people. the wise contradict themselves.', 40, 0), (337438, 'Don''t let sex make you a mother before love makes you a wife.', 55154, 0), (337439, 'Bring the past, but only if you can build from it.', 55155, 0), (337440, 'may be wiser to everything to see and understand what it left behind', 4259, 0), (337441, 'Wise people are only wise because they have lived many lives before.', 46210, 0), (337442, 'If you are a sparrow, don’t attack the eagle; be wise! If you are an eagle, don’t attack the sparrow; be just!', 3701, 0), (337443, 'Truth exists for the wise, beauty for the feeling heart.', 1988, 0), (337444, 'Some People Are Wise, And Some Are Otherwise.', 55156, 0), (337445, 'There is a time to speak up, and a time to be silent. A time to read and a time to write. A time to learn and a time to teach. A time to listen and time to be heard. A time to lose and a time to gain. And for all of these things the time in now', 55157, 0), (337446, 'When the ignorant have become numerous or powerful enough, they have been referred to by a special name. This names is ''the Wise''.', 4860, 0), (337447, 'Surely this is what death would be like: nothingness, oblivion, as the world continued to turn, heedless of her absence.', 6477, 0), (337448, 'To be yourself in a world that is constantly trying to make you something else is the greatest 